cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper proposes an end-to-end short utterances speech language identification approach based on a Long Short Term Memory (LSTM) neural network which is special suitable for SLD application in intelligent vehicles.
- cs.SD (Sound) is also likely as the paper deals with speech processing and uses a phase vocoder based time-scale modification method to improve SLD accuracy.
- cs.LG (Learning) is another possible category as the paper uses transfer learning and deep neural network (DNN) bottleneck features for LSTM training.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible category as the paper proposes an AI-based approach for language identification.
